# Tier B P0.1 — semantic spine behavior-entry harness (test-only).
# Concatenated after azl_security_for_interpreter_spine.azl and before
# azl/runtime/interpreter/azl_interpreter.azl. Entry component: ::azl.spine.behavior.entry
# links the real interpreter, then:
#   - two emit interpret (same code) — second pass exercises in-file tok_cache + ast_cache hits;
#   - third emit interpret (two-line user code) — split("\n"), parse loop, two say executes;
#   - fourth emit interpret (three-line user code) — deeper parse loop + three say executes;
#   - fifth emit interpret (four-line user code) — deeper parse loop + four say executes;
#     markers Q5a–Q5d are intentionally short: semantic spine Var.v / ::ast.nodes budget is 255 bytes (see minimal_runtime ::parse_tokens).
#   - sixth emit interpret (single-line literal say) — another full interpret→tokenize→parse→execute after smoke5; stdout marker AZL_S6_ONLY.
#   - seventh emit interpret (same code as sixth) — second tok_cache + ast_cache round-trip on AZL_S6_ONLY source (mirrors smoke/smoke2).
#   - eighth emit interpret (single-line literal say, new code) — distinct marker AZL_S8_MARK; cache miss on tok/ast for this snippet.
#   - ninth emit interpret (set global then say) — exercises ::execute_ast set|… row on real interpret→parse→execute chain (not covered by say-only smokes).
#   - tenth emit interpret (bare emit user statement) — exercises ::execute_emit → ::emit_event_resolved on the real file path (📡 line + Emitted: in ::result).
#   - eleventh emit interpret (emit … with { k: v }) — exercises payload path in ::emit_event_resolved (AZL_EMIT_WITH_PAYLOAD) on the real file path.
#   - twelfth emit interpret (on name { say … } then name()) — exercises top-level ::parse_tokens + ::execute_ast function registration + ::execute_call on the real file path.
#   - fourteenth emit interpret (if ( true ) { say … }) — ::parse_if_statement / ::execute_if_statement; spine ::parse_tokens emits if| row; host execute_ast branches.
#   - fifteenth emit interpret (if ( false ) { … } otherwise { say … }) — single-statement alternate branch; skipped then-body.
#   - sixteenth emit interpret (if ( false ) { … } otherwise { two says }) — ordered multi-statement otherwise body (AZL_SPINE_P16_A then AZL_SPINE_P16_B); skipped then-body AZL_SPINE_P16_BAD.
#   - seventeenth emit interpret — set ::azl_spine_p17 = true then if ( ::azl_spine_p17 ) { … } otherwise { … }: condition is evaluated (not a literal in the if parens); then-branch only; AZL_SPINE_P17_BAD must not run.
#   - eighteenth emit interpret — set ::azl_spine_p18 = false then if ( ::azl_spine_p18 ) { … } otherwise { … }: evaluated falsey global; otherwise only; AZL_SPINE_P18_BAD must not run.
#   - nineteenth emit interpret — evaluated truthy global; multi-statement then-branch (two say lines, same shape as P16); AZL_SPINE_P19_A before AZL_SPINE_P19_B; AZL_SPINE_P19_BAD must not run.
#   - twentieth emit interpret — evaluated falsey global; multi-statement otherwise-branch (two say lines); AZL_SPINE_P20_A before AZL_SPINE_P20_B; AZL_SPINE_P20_BAD must not run.
#   - twenty-first emit interpret — `if ( ::azl_spine_p21 == 1 )` expression condition (not lone `::var`); AZL_SPINE_P21_IF; AZL_SPINE_P21_BAD must not run.
#   - twenty-second emit interpret — `if ( ::azl_spine_p22 == 2 )` false expression path; AZL_SPINE_P22_ELSE; AZL_SPINE_P22_BAD must not run.
#   - twenty-third emit interpret — `if ( ::azl_spine_p23 == 2 )` true expression path, multi-statement then (P23_A then P23_B); P23_BAD must not run.
#   - twenty-fourth emit interpret — `if ( ::azl_spine_p24 == 3 )` false expression path, multi-statement otherwise (P24_A then P24_B); P24_BAD must not run.
#   - twenty-fifth emit interpret — two sequential ifs on ::azl_spine_p25 (true then false); P25_T before P25_F; P25_BAD1 and P25_BAD2 must not run.
#   - twenty-sixth emit interpret — nested if inside then-branch; P26_OUTER then P26_INNER; P26_BAD1 and P26_BAD2 must not run.
#   - twenty-seventh emit interpret — nested if inside otherwise-branch; P27_OUTER then P27_INNER; P27_BAD1 and P27_BAD2 must not run.
#   - twenty-eighth emit interpret — outer expression `== 2`, inner `== 3` nested if in then; P28_OUTER then P28_INNER; P28_BAD1 and P28_BAD2 must not run.
#   - twenty-ninth emit interpret — three sequential ifs on ::azl_spine_p29 (true / false / true); P29_A then P29_B then P29_C; BAD1–BAD3 must not run.
#   - thirtieth emit interpret — multi-statement then on `== 1` then second if `== 2` false → otherwise C; P30_A then P30_B then P30_C; P30_BAD1 and P30_BAD2 must not run.
#   - thirty-first emit interpret — evaluated outer true; nested `if ( true )` multi-statement then; P31_OUTER then P31_A then P31_B; P31_BAD1 and P31_BAD2 must not run.
#   - thirty-second emit interpret — evaluated outer false; nested `if ( false )` multi-statement otherwise; P32_OUTER then P32_A then P32_B; P32_BAD1 and P32_BAD2 must not run.
#   - thirty-third emit interpret — outer `== 1` then nested `== 2` false → INNER; P33_OUTER then P33_INNER; P33_BAD1 and P33_BAD2 must not run.
#   - thirty-fourth emit interpret — three nested levels (L1/L2/L3); P34_BAD1/BAD2/BAD3 must not run.
#   - thirty-fifth emit interpret — four alternating if outcomes on ::azl_spine_p35 (A/B/C/D); P35_BAD1–BAD4 must not run.
#   - thirty-sixth emit interpret — expression multi-statement then (`== 2`) then second if `== 3` false → multi-statement otherwise; P36_A through P36_D in order; BAD1/BAD2 must not run.
#   - thirty-seventh emit interpret — outer otherwise with OUTER say then set true then inner if; P37_OUTER then P37_INNER; BAD1/BAD2 must not run.
#   - thirty-eighth emit interpret — mutate ::azl_spine_p38 then `== 1` / `== 2` branches in sequence; P38_A then P38_B then P38_C; BAD1–BAD3 must not run.
#   - thirty-ninth emit interpret — double-nested mixed true/false (L1 → inner otherwise → L2 → inner then → L3); P39_BAD1/BAD2/BAD3 must not run.
#   - fortieth emit interpret — mixed `== 5` / `== 6` / `::azl_spine_p40_flag` / `== 5` again; P40_A then B then C then D; BAD1–BAD4 must not run.
#   - forty-first emit interpret — otherwise OUTER then set `::azl_spine_p41_n = 7` then inner `== 7`; P41_OUTER then P41_INNER; BAD1/BAD2 must not run.
#   - forty-second emit interpret — plain then, `::azl_spine_p42_n == 8` false → B, set false then multi-statement otherwise C/D; P42_A then B then C then D; BAD1–BAD3 must not run.
#   - forty-third emit interpret — triple sequential `==` after `set` mutation each time; P43_A then P43_B then P43_C; BAD1–BAD3 must not run.
#   - forty-fourth emit interpret — outer otherwise L1, inner otherwise L2, inner-inner then L3; P44_L1 then L2 then L3; BAD1–BAD3 must not run.
#   - forty-fifth through fifty-fourth — P45 set+inner == after mutation; P46 five-way plain alternation; P47 expr then expr else then flag; P48 outer then multi-statement inner otherwise; P49 outer otherwise + set + multi-statement then; P50 three-level mixed ==; P51 A then B/C nested otherwise; P52 mutation flip + multi-statement then; P53 outer false inner true + expr else; P54 five-step mixed finale.

